This paper deals with limited feedback beamforming in wireless communication systems, which involves the transmission and compression of channel state information (CSI). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also involves the design of algorithms and systems for wireless communication, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also considers the impact of feedback delay on system performance, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves the use of multiple-input-multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical models and analytical results, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
